package a44qJavaBean_Class;

public class aSample {
	
	/*
	 1. What is POJO class?
	 * POJO - Plain old java object.
	 * It is simple java object, which is not bound by any special restrictions.
	 
	 Rules for a class to be called as POJO class 
	 1. It must be public.
	 2. It is recommended to make the properties (instance variables) as private for improved security.
	 3. It can have Getters & Setters in order to access properties.
	 4. It should not implement any interfaces.
	 5. It should not extend any classes
	 6. It should not have annotations specified.
	 7. Mostly main method was not there in POJO classes.
	 */
	
	/*
	 1. What is Java Bean class?
	 * Java Bean class is extended version of a POJO class.
	 * It is also reffered as a serializable POJO class.
	 
	 Rules for a class to be called as Java Bean class 
	 1. It should implement seralizable interfaces.
	 2. It should have a no-args constructor.
	 3. All the properties (instance variables) should be private.
	 5. It should not extend any classes
	 6. It should not have annotations specified.
	 7. Mostly main method was not there in POJO classes.
	 */

}
